SUBJECT: Oskar, Senior Account Manager ( SaaS Implementation)
CONTENT: Hello Oskar,  One of my favourite clients in Paris; a global organization experiencing exceptional development and international growth that drives impact for brands, packaging and beyond, are looking for a new Senior Account Manager.   The role is located in Paris (hybrid) with a competitive salary and benefits package.   Here are some details on this specific role below:  -Building relationships based on mutual trust and open communication with Customer sponsors, regional/functional divisions and key client stakeholders. -Gathering and analysing feedback about system usage and satisfaction levels to identify bottlenecks, pain points and opportunities for improvement. -Overseeing the process for capturing and analysing customer requests for new functionality. -Liaising with the product and development teams to follow up on developments. -Overseeing the account management: *Monitoring budget, revenue and KPIs. *Managing the invoicing for the client. *Cross-selling and upselling on Mediabox-related features and specific development.  Want to know more? SUBJECT: Consultancy on Embedded Finance - Paid Project
CONTENT: Dear Oskar Ablimit,  I am contacting you from Guidepoint - Germany, an expert network that helps our clients connect with relevant industry professionals like yourself for their research and due diligence needs.  Currently, I am running a project in which our client, a leading management consultancy, is doing a market study on embedded finance, with the main focus on Europe & US. We are looking at experts who are familiar with the merchant acquiring process at the platform and who have a view on the current use of embedded finance products (e.g., Buy-Now-Pay later, Merchant Finance, Card issuance, Current account issuance), and/or the plans to offer these services to the merchants on the platforms.  Given your experience, I thought you would be a great fit for this request. Consultations typically last 60 min, are scheduled around your availability and you are compensated at your desired rate. As a range, our experts would indicate an average rate of 150-300 EUR/hour, but you can specify your own desired rate.  As a matter of policy, our clients will not be asking you to discuss any confidential or material non-public information.   You can access the project via the link below. On the first page you will be able to fill your contact information and desired compensation rate. On the second page you will see a list of screening questions designed to help you gain a better understanding of what the client would like to discuss.    http://gpt.io/rwSLtX91  Do not hesitate to contact me for any further details. Best,  Alexandra Moukhametova Strategic Research Associate at Guidepoint

SUBJECT: Collaborating with Tencent in and out of China
CONTENT: Thanks for your attention. I am Oskar, a strategic account manager from Tencent Cloud Europe Team, I mainly support Europe based customers in and out of China with the Tencent ecosystem. I am sending this email to see if we have any opportunity to work together. We will be the perfect partner you are looking for if you have any of these cases below: ‚Ä¢ You have a business in China and need to reach out to more and more customers to expand your market. ‚Ä¢ You have end users in China, but application is hosted outside of China and need a solution to accelerate the cross-border connection without worrying about the compliance issue. ‚Ä¢ You need to host your applications in China to serve the local customers better. You have a tight budget in terms of cloud consumption ‚Ä¢ You want to be regulated properly in terms of MPLS and obtain the necessary licenses such as ICP, EDI, CDN, IDC, ext. ‚Ä¢ You need the best cloud providers and partners in terms of gaming and live streaming ‚Ä¢ You need to host your SaaS without having the right license and expand your channels in China ‚Ä¢ You need to distribute your content globally with cheaper and more reliable CDN solutions. ‚Ä¢ Any help with China expansion or need any support from Tencent ecosystem We can offer the basic free consulting in terms of topics above and direct you to the right resources if needed. Here are some links for you to take a quick look at. Based on your situation, we could have a deep dive discussion if you are interested. ‚Ä¢ Tencent Cloud Introduction: https://customer-sharing-1301327510.cos.eu-frankfurt.myqcloud.com/Tencent%20Cloud%20Introduction%20062021.pptx ‚Ä¢ Tencent ecosystem introduction: https://customer-sharing-1301327510.cos.eu-frankfurt.myqcloud.com/Tencent%20Ecosystem%20Introduction_022021.pptx  Regards,  Oskar Abulimit Senior Strategy Sales Manager Tencent Cloud Europe +33688773656 oskarabt@tencent.com WeChat ID: askar6820306 |LinkedIn- https://www.linkedin.com/in/awsoskar/

Dear Oskar,


My name is Irina Deneanu, and I'm an Associate Director at IE University, one of the leading European higher education institutions. 

 

In name of IE Law School I am pleased to invite you to our Virtual Legal Challenge on July 23rd at 10.00h CET.

 

FIf you are interested in studying a master program at IE Law School, don‚Äôt miss out on this opportunity to win a scholarship for one of our programs.

 

The legal case that participants must solve, will focus on law and technology and the new trends in data protection. Students will have an introductory master class with Professor Antonios Kouroutakis where we will explore:

- Basic features and key aspects of the General Data Protection Regulation.

- The legal challenges that arise with data mostly related to data property, security, and data protection laws.

- Key business models in relation to data collections and processing: from cloud to blockchain, from analytics to artificial intelligence and robotics.


After the session, you will receive the case and must solve it in 48h, sending your answer to admissions.law@ie.edu. Please include your name and surname + LLM Challenge as the email subject. The winner will be granted a 30% scholarship applicable to the tuition fees of one of the following programs:

- Master in Global Corporate Compliance (Full-Time & Part-Time).

- Executive LLM

- LLM in International Business Law

- Master in Legal Tech


Agenda

Tuesday, July 23rd, 10:00hrs CEST 

Virtual Legal Challenge

Online


Please register here as places are limited.


We look forward to meeting you soon!


Best Regards,


Irina Deneanu

asia-pacific@ie.edu

Oskar,  Thank you so much for accepting my invitation.  I‚Äôm replying to tell you a little more about what I do and how it could bring value to you.    I coach non-Americans who live around the world. They all work for tech firms such as Amazon and AWS, Dell, SAP, Accenture, Microsoft, and Google.  I don‚Äôt have a program, a model, or use some other ‚Äúcanned‚Äù, predetermined way to work with a client.  Instead, together, we create a customized program to meet his needs, for example, to stand out among peers, build executive presence, lead and inspire others, recognize blind spots, strengthen brand, manage up, exceed goals, make big impact, decide ‚ÄúWhat‚Äôs next for me?‚Äù and so on.    The coaching is completely confidential.  I do not work for your company, so I am an objective sounding board, who has no agenda and no vested interest other than to be completely devoted to supporting you.    In over 20 years of coaching, I've learned that showing what I do is so much better than describing it.  To that end, if you are seriously interested in coaching, I offer a 30 to 40-minute Free Sample Coaching Session so you can experience first-hand how I coach and how, working together, might add value to your career as well as your life. SUBJECT: [Google Job Opportunity] Cloud Business Development Manager - Shenzhen
CONTENT: Dear Oskar,   Hope this email finds you well. By way of introduction, I am a Cloud Recruiter at Google and responsible for cloud roles hiring in Greater China.  I came across your profile, your education background and experience look impressive and could be a good fit for the Google Cloud BD Manager role at Google Shenzhen.   About Google Cloud:  Google Cloud helps millions of employees and organizations empower their employees, serve their customers, and build what‚Äôs next for their business ‚Äî all with technology built in the cloud.   About the role:  As a Business Development Manager, you'll leverage existing relationships with C-level executives, develop new relationships and act as a trusted business partner to deeply understand their unique company challenges and goals. You will advocate the innovative power of our products to make organizations more productive, collaborative, and mobile.   As a member of the Google Cloud team, you will inspire leading companies, schools, and government agencies to work smarter with Google tools like G Suite, Search, and Chrome. You will advocate the innovative power of our products to make organizations more productive, collaborative, and mobile.   Please let me know if you are interested to have a more detailed discussion.   Look forward to hearing from you.  Best Regards,   Tatiana Lyskova  Cloud Recruiter at Google

From a general perspective, make sure you move forward when you don‚Äôt feel challenged in your current role; when your learning curve is coming to a slow/no growth point. What does the next step mean in terms of leadership requirements? I often tell my talents, that once they become more senior and with ‚Äúpeople‚Äù responsibility, their job changes. I‚Äôd still expect the same sales performance while handling a team and additional tasks.  If you‚Äôre happy in your role, love what your doing on a daily basis and don‚Äôt think that a ‚Äúnext step‚Äù is really necessary at this moment, I would always go for a ‚Äúsalary adjustment‚Äù rather than promotion. It‚Äôs a great feeling to be recognized for good work monetarily. Hope this helps a bit!

SUBJECT: LinkedIn Learning - help your employees learn the skills for today and tomorrow!

LinkedIn Leanring can give you a different view on the above questions with our big data and AI combined Intelligent Learning Tool.   I have great stories to share with you on how do we help companies to do digital transformation, and I am eager to understand your L&D strategies and see how LinkedIn Learning can align with your needs.   Hope you are open for a 20 minutes call anytime this or next week. Appreciate if you can share with me your work contact number and preferred time.   Have a great week ahead.   Regards. Nice to meet you here! This is Michael from iPinYou HR team. We are now seeking for a potential sales and business develop talent just like you to support the roaring digital marketing business . I have seen your impressive experience via LinkedIn, just wonder whether or not you are interested in iPinYou, our team, our business or our position. So could you share with me your contact number and email address, that I will reach out to you for more communication.   About iPinYou, iPinYou is the first one introducing RTB technology to China market. Ever since, iPinYou has continued bringing innovation to digital advertising trading in China, including PDB, PMP, mobile, OTT programmatic buying. Relying on world-class real- time bidding (RTB) architecture and algorithm as well as advanced proprietary audience targeting technology, iPinYou helps thousands of brands in China to achieve robust programmatic buying practice. iPinYou has formed a world's leading research team on data mining and machine learning algorithm, introduced leading big data research methods in the field of advertising technology, and independently developed OptimusTM system. This system accesses to China's largest Internet user behavior data and has patented on its audience analysis model and ad optimization algorithm. OPTIMUSTM system supports programmatic ad buying on PC banner, video and mobile as well as cross-screen of these three. Almost all leading brands in industries such as FMCG, automobile, IT, finance, e-commerce, and gaming are using iPinYou programmatic buying platform to uplift their brand awareness and improve their operational efficiency. The platform has successfully served thousands of branding advertisers and tens of thousands of small and medium-sized enterprises. According to authoritative data, iPinYou represents 59.8% market share of brand programmatic buying in China. The future of advertising lies in Data + Technology.

CONVERSATION TITLE: Learn how to build an effective ABM strategy
CONTENT:
Hi Oskar,


Account-based marketing (ABM) is all the talk in B2B technology, and rightfully so. In recent years, ABM has emerged as a core strategy for early stage startups and industry leaders alike because it‚Äôs uniquely capable of accelerating revenue growth and driving product adoption. With ABM capabilities expanding and more brands adopting this approach, the question becomes, how can tech marketers embrace ABM to engage with key audiences and drive better alignment with sales?


Watch our on-demand webinar to learn the framework for designing an effective ABM strategy, including how to develop content that drives action.


We'll cover:


  • Top tips that tech marketers should consider when developing a successful ABM strategy, according to our most frequently asked questions
  • How to approach content personalization, with examples of tech brands who‚Äôve successfully done so
  • Q&A to address your most burning questions


Enjoy the webinar!


Best,

Purna Virji

Senior Content Solutions Consultant

LinkedIn Marketing Solutions

CONVERSATION TITLE: You‚Äôre invited to Elastic and AWS DevDay

CONTENT:
Hi Oskar,


I work in Admissions at the Quantic School of Business and Technology. We offer a selective Executive MBA that is challenging the model of elite traditional business schools. Your profile closely aligns with that of our ideal candidate and I‚Äôd like to invite you to apply.


Our students and alumni work in leading companies ‚Äî IBM, Google, and Uber, to name a few. Over 100 Google executives have enrolled in the past year while three of our MBA students were recently honored as Forbes 30 Under 30. We also have over 50 graduates from your alma mater, George Washington University - you might even know a few! While many of your fellow alumni have already enrolled, please note we are not formally affiliated with the university.


Our accredited 13-month Executive MBA is online and app-based so you can truly learn on-the-go. It‚Äôs also a small fraction of the cost of a traditional program, with many students receiving full funding from their companies through existing HR tuition reimbursement policies.


Next step? Just sign up! Once you‚Äôve done that, you can start your application, sample actual MBA courses, or preview our extensive alumni network.


quantic.edu/invite/GWU

Best regards, 

Kristina Wessel

Director of Admissions

CONVERSATION TITLE: Meet the future of your business in Latin America
CONTENT:
Hello Oskar, I have exciting news to share with you.


For the last 9 years we‚Äôve been connecting global companies to Latin America through payment solutions. As a company that calls the region home, this makes us fully aware of how challenging it can be for Alibaba Cloud to reach this market.


LatAm‚Äôs complex and hyper fragmented market presents many challenges in terms of payments, tax, regulations and integrations that can be difficult to navigate if you aren‚Äôt in the region. To add a layer to this, operational models have changed in the past years and will continue evolving.


To offer a singular solution to make expansion smoother in LatAm has always been a dream of ours. Now, I can proudly say it is a reality.


Regardless of how Alibaba Cloud does business in the region, EBANX ONE is the solution to reach Latin America, today and in the future. The flexibility you need to grow your business in the region in a fast, and localized way is here.

CONVERSATION TITLE: a 10,000% ROI opportunity, despite the recession?
CONTENT:
Hi Oskar,


Internet-related IPOs one can make millions of dollars on a small investment. For example, Mike Walsh and Oren Michels earned $25M million each on their $5K investments in Uber. Such investment opportunities are rarely accessible to individual investors and investment banks and VC funds keep the best deals to themselves.


IT businesses can grow remarkably fast. Zoom has reached the valuation of $160B, TikTok - $75B, Salesforce - $250B.


At TransparentBusiness, we decided to open our Global Private Offering to individuals in order to create a large international network of "brand ambassadors" and prepare the company for a successful IPO next year. Here's the nature of the opportunity I offer for your consideration:


Four billion people have been ordered to stay home due to the coronavirus pandemic and executives around the world are discovering that managing remote workers blindly is as tricky as conducting an orchestra without seeing or hearing the musicians. Never before a market as large has appeared so fast.


We have a solution. It‚Äôs robust, acclaimed, and infinitely scalable. Designated by Citigroup as "the Top People Management Solution", our TransparentBusiness platform boosts the productivity of remote work by making it easy to monitor and coordinate. Our investors include current and former executives of Morgan Stanley, Merrill Lynch, J.P. Morgan, Stifel, Bank of America, Barclays Global Investors, UBS, Wells Fargo, Goldman Sachs, Citigroup, Deutsche Bank, Microsoft, Telefonica, EY, Deloitte, IBM, LinkedIn, Microsoft and Accenture. Our objective is to make TransparentBusiness synonymous with the categories of Business Transparency and remote workforce management, globally.


The minimum investment is $5,000 and the maximum is $1M per person. The current stock price is $2 per share. As outlined in our fundraising strategy summary, we plan to go public on the New York Stock Exchange in the Fourth Quarter of 2021. At TransparentBusiness.com/invest you can review the detailed information about this opportunity and purchase our equity while this round remains open.


Looking forward to hearing from you,


With very best wishes,


Alex Konanykhin

CEO, TransparentBusiness, Inc.

AK@TransparentBusiness.com

Linkedin.com/in/konanykhin

Bio: Konanykhin.com

San Francisco, CA

Dear Oskar,


I'm Liang YU, the Director of Admission from Peking University, Guanghua MBA. Peking University was ranked the 1st University in China Mainland in Economics and Business by US News 2020. For professional who is looking for opportunities to advance their careers in China and the wider global economy, Guanghua MBA program is a perfect fit.

 

Our program is designed as a 2-year, full-time program taught in English tailored for high potential professionals who aspire to become international business leaders.

 

The program can offer you:

  • Excellent Career Opportunities: With the help of Career Development Office, students can not only receive specialized, individual and systematic career advice, planning, training and job placement services, but also benefit from PKU‚Äôs firm connection with over 600 global recruiting partners and get unique career opportunities. 

Our Round 2 deadline is Dec. 18th. 2020, Round 3 deadline is Feb. 22nd, 2021. We welcome all the applicants to apply for our program! If you are interested, remember to download our brochure for more information.


Best regards,

Liang

Hello Oskar,On behalf of IE, one of the leading European higher education institutions, we would love for you to join us in Beijing for our Master Class in The Future of NOW by Ramsés Gallego.Change is a constant in today’s world. Organizations are being pressed with time-to-market issues while they should a have time-to-value perspective. In an epoch where technology is pervasive and you can hardly find businesses that do not depend on technology, we should face change as one critical variable in the planning of enterprise strategy.By attending this session, you will enhance your perception on the importance of time when designing, planning and executing a business strategy. The difference between strategy and tactics will be mentioned as well as the need of adapting to change in a world with no secrets, no barriers, no frontiers. You will gain a deeper understanding on the issues of adaptability, trustability and reliability and, more important, will discover that we are living in the future.AGENDA The Future of NOWRenaissance Beijing Capital Hotel 61 Dongsanhuan Middle Road, Chaoyang District, Beijing, 100022Wednesday, August 30From: 19:30 to 21:30With a background education in Business Administration (MBA) and Law, Ramsés is a +20-year security professional with deep expertise in the Risk Management and Governance areas. Ramsés is now Strategist & Evangelist at the Office of the CTO in Symantec. Previously he worked with Dell Security and CA Technologies, SurfControl in Spain and Portugal, and also at Entelgy. He is honored to have been the Chair for ISACA’s ISRM Conference and part of the Program Committee for the events SecureCloud 2010 and 2012.We look forward to meeting you soon!Alex Buriel Director - IE China Officealex.buriel@ie.edu
